JOB SUMMARY: Responsible for kitchen operations including the preparation of meals, appropriate inventory management and enforcing food handling and sanitation guidelines. We prefer young candidates. <br>
<br>
ESSENTIAL JOB FUNCTIONS :<br>
1.	Implements food and preparation based on guidelines established by Villa Nova. <br>
•	Determines ingredients and weighs and measures portions for quantities required.<br>
•	Plans and coordinates preparation and cooking times to insure foods are ready for serving times. <br>
•	Monitors cooking process by regulating temperatures, turning, basting, and seasoning as needed.<br>
•	Operates a variety of electric or mechanical food service equipment such as mixers, grinders, and dicers in compliance with safety regulations. Maintains equipment and work area in a safe and sanitary condition.<br>
<br>
2.	Maintains a high standard of sanitation in the kitchen area at all times. <br>
3.     Must be highly skilled and posses basic culinary knowledge in order to perform the job. <br>
4.     Must have good knife skills and knowledge of time management in terms of preparing food to the ticket (KOT). <br>
<br>
NECESSARY SKILLS &amp; KNOWLEDGE - <br>
<br>
•   Ability to work effectively in a team environment.<br>
•   Ability to maintain quality, safety and infection control standards.<br>
•   Knowledge of the characteristics of various raw and cooked foods to determine freshness and to judge quality of final               product.<br>
•  Skills to plan the coordination and timing/sequence of steps needed to have a number of menu items ready for serving at mealtime without overcooking or waste.<br>
•  Ability to prepare food according to menu specifications and adjust recipes according to number of servings needed.<br>
•  Ability to maintain a high level of sanitation in the kitchen area at all times according to sanitation requirements.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
QUALIFICATIONS:<br>
<br>
1. Minimum 2-3 years of culinary experience / industry working experience.<br>
    (Do not preferred McDonald/Subway/Wendy's kitchen experience)<br>
2. Minimum 2-3 years of education in culinary field. (Any Diploma/Degree/Course in Culinary will work)<br>
3.Must have food handlers card and TAM's card. <br>
4. High School Diploma.<br>
5. Must have good knife skills and quick physical movements in kitchen. <br>
6. Must ready to work on some of the big nights of the year i.e. Christmas Evening, New Years's Evening &amp; Valentines Day. <br>
<br>
WORK ENVIRONMENT - <br>
<br>
The work involves constant standing and walking as well as moving and lifting of objects.<br>
Exposed to steam, fumes, cooking odors, burns, cuts, and extreme temperatures when entering walk-in refrigerators. <br>
You must have good team working skills in terms of working in this kitchen. We work from Tuesday's to Saturdays from 3pm till 10 pm. <br>
<br>
Interested and committed candidates can send us their resumes along with their working phone numbers and email id's at - <br>
villanovacatering@gmail.com <br>
<br>
And we will get back to you or call you for an interview.<br>
    </section>

